<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Trivial bug in FlashMessenger class - if there are no messages method getIterator returns result of call of nonexistent function ArrayObject() instead of returning newly created object of class ArrayObject(). Please, replace code</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    public function getIterator()
    {
        if ($this-&gt;hasMessages()) {
            return new ArrayObject($this-&gt;getMessages());
        }

        return ArrayObject();
    }
</code></pre>

<p>with</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    public function getIterator()
    {
        if ($this-&gt;hasMessages()) {
            return new ArrayObject($this-&gt;getMessages());
        }

        return new ArrayObject();
    }
</code></pre>

